extends DistCol<T>
    DistCol with additional features allowing it to replicate some range of values held by a process onto other processes

    • Method Detail

      • allreduce

        public void allreduce(BiConsumer<PrimitiveOutput,T> pack,
                      BiConsumer<PrimitiveInput,T> unpack,
                      mpi.Op op)
        Conduct allreduce operation on shared chunks using MPI reduce operation.

        This variant cannot handle object data, but is faster than allreduce(Function, BiConsumer) in many cases.

        The core idea consists in converting each individual T object into a number of long, int, and double, perform an MPI primitive "all reduce" reduction on these raw types, and modify the T elements contained by the CachableChunkedList based on the resulting PrimitiveInput.

        The number of raw type values of each type stored into the PrimitiveOutput must be the same for all T elements. The unpack closure supplied as second parameter must also extract the same number of raw type data (even if such raw type data is eventually unused to modify the T element) to preserve the consistency of the data in relation to the individual T element being processed.
        =========================================================================
        code sample 

         class Element {
     double d1, d2;
     int i;
 }

 cachableChunkedList.allreduce((PrimitiveOutput out, Element e) -> {
     out.writeDouble(e.d1);
     out.writeDouble(e.d2);
     out.writeInt(e.i);
 }, (PrimitiveInput in, Element e) -> {
     e.d1 = in.readDouble(); // Match the unpack order with the pack closure above
     e.d2 = in.readDouble();
     in.readInt(); // (For examples purposes) the int is eventually not used to modify `e`,
                   // but in.readInt needs to be called regardless
 }, MPI.SUM);

        =========================================================================
        Parameters:
        pack - the function that receives an element and extracts data to transfer and reduce with other places.
        unpack - the function that receives a local element and raw data that was reduced between the hosts using MPI.
        op - the MPI reduction operation used to merge the

      • getDistribution

        public LongRangeDistribution getDistribution()
        Returns a newly created snapshot of the current distribution of this collection as a LongRangeDistribution. This returned distribution's contents will become out-of-date if the contents of this class are relocated, added, and/or removed. The distribution does not include shared ranges.

        If you need a LongRangeDistribution to remain up-to-date with the actual distribution of a DistCol, considers using DistCol.registerDistribution(UpdatableDistribution). By registering a LongRangeDistribution, changes in the distribution of entries of this DistCol will be reflected in the LongRangeDistribution object when the distribution information of DistCol is updated and synchronized between hosts using DistCol.updateDist(). This is more efficient than allocating a new LongRangeDistribution object each time the distribution of the distributed collection changes.

        Overrides:
        getDistribution in class DistCol<T>
        Returns:
        a new LongRangeDistribution object representing the current distribution of this collection

      • share

        public void share()
        Calls for the sharing of chunks between the local handles of the CachableChunkedList, but with this local handle not sharing any chunk with the other handles. Instead, it will only receive the chunked shared by the other handles.

      • share

        public void share(CollectiveRelocator.Allgather mm)
        conduct broadcast operation on chunks that are not shared with other places yet. The user must call each of the share methods of a cachable chunked list in all the place belonging to the place group. This method should not be called simultaneously with other collective methods. The caller place is treated as the owner even if the chunks become shared.

        Note 1: if you want to share all the local chunks, please call share()

        Note 2: if you want to specify multiple ranges, please use share(List).

        Note 3: if you don't want to share any local chunks from the called place, please specify an empty range or an empty list of ranges.

        Note 4: if you want to conduct the relocation process of multiple cachable chunked lists using the same ObjectOutput(Stream), please prepare an instance of CollectiveRelocator.Allgather first and call the relocation methods of the cachable chunked lists in the same order specifying the collective relocator as a parameter, and finally call the execute method of the relocator.

        Parameters:
        mm - You can relocate multiple cachable chunked lists using the same collective relocator, specified with mm.

        Note 4: if you want to conduct the relocation process of multiple cachable chunked lists using the same ObjectOutput(Stream), please prepare an instance of CollectiveRelocator.Allgather first and call the relocation methods of the cachable chunked lists in the same order specifying the collective relocator as a parameter, and finally call the execute method of the relocator.

        Parameters:
        range - The library scans the range and exports (the parts of) the local chunks in the range.

      • share

        public void share(LongRange range,
                  CollectiveRelocator.Allgather mm)
        conduct broadcast operation on chunks that are not shared with other places yet. The user must call each of the share methods of a cachable chunked list in all the place belonging to the place group. This method should not be called simultaneously with other collective methods. The caller place is treated as the owner even if the chunks become shared.

        Note 1: if you want to share all the local chunks, please call share()

        Note 2: if you want to specify multiple ranges, please use share(List).

        Note 3: if you don't want to share any local chunks from the called place, please specify an empty range or an empty list of ranges.

        Note 4: if you want to conduct the relocation process of multiple cachable chunked lists using the same ObjectOutput(Stream), please prepare an instance of CollectiveRelocator.Allgather first and call the relocation methods of the cachable chunked lists in the same order specifying the collective relocator as a parameter, and finally call the execute method of the relocator.

        Parameters:
        range - The library scans the range and exports (the parts of) the local chunks in the range.
        mm - You can relocate multiple cachable chunked lists using the same collective relocator, specified with mm.

      • sharedChunks

        public ChunkedList<T> sharedChunks()
        Returns ChunkedList contains chunks that are already shared within the place group. The returned shared chunkedList has an unmodifiable structure. Operations such as add and remove cannot be performed.
        Returns:
        ChunkedList contains chunks that are already shared

      • writeReplace

        public Object writeReplace()
                    throws ObjectStreamException
        Description copied from interface: DistributedCollection
        Method used to create an object which will be transferred to a remote place.

        This method is present in interface DistributedCollection to force the implementation in implementing classes. Implementation should return a LazyObjectReference instance capable of initializing the local handle of the implementing class on the remote place
